From: becker@super.org (Donald J. Becker)
Subject: Re: MCA Support > Please
Date: Thu, 4 Nov 1993 15:18:01 GMT

In article <1993Nov1.214324.5091@aston.ac.uk>,
Mark Evans <evansmp@mb48059.aston.ac.uk> wrote:
>Uri Blumenthal (uri@yktnews.UUCP) wrote:
>: From article <2avec1$8sv@hecate.umd.edu>, by ceham@w3eax.umd.edu (Maurice De Vidts NE3S):
...
>: Two things are to be done to get Linux up and runnng on MCA:
>:      1) ESDI support, publication 68X2234, form # S68X-2234.
>:      2) SCSI support, pubs 68X2397 and 68X2365.
...
>: To get display to work with anything better than 640x480x16 one
>: will need to port some XGA and/or V256C (ThinkPad-700 chip).
>
>Also microchannel ethernet cards.
>I have only seen BICC and WD cards for MCA, though there may 
>be others.

I don't know what interface the BICC and WD MCA cards use so I can't comment
on them. There is also the 3c529 from 3Com.  It would work with the 3c509
driver if I wrote the MCA-specific probe code for it.

If someone cares about this they should probably write to Linus and ask him to
put "CONFIG_MCA" into the 'config.in' file, and set a global variable like
"int MCA_bus;" in init/main.c.  If those existed I might put in the MCA
ethercard probes when I update drivers.  (Of course the new code would be
completely untested, since I try to avoid buying gratuitously incompatible
hardware like MCA.)

-- 

Donald Becker                                          becker@super.org
IDA Supercomputing Research Center
17100 Science Drive, Bowie MD 20715                        301-805-7482

